subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
The female examined (
Figs. 26
, 
29–39
) fits the redescription by 
Linnavuori (1994)
, although the scutellum seems less bifid apically (see 
Figs. 36–37
) and the membrane of the hemelytra is uniformly milky-brown and of the same colour as the posterior portion of the clavus (
Fig. 26
). The clavus has sparse pilosity and corium relatively dense pilosity (
Fig. 38
). The membrane reaches the posterior 2/3 of mediotergite VII, leaving the apex of the dorsum free (
Fig. 26
).
